name: Happy Hearts Learning Academy
details:
We believe that all children are unique and can learn through the cooperation amongst our highly trained staff. Happy Hearts Learning Academy activities will enhance childrens physical, emotional, social, cultural, and academic growth. Happy heart's children learn to think independently, problem solve and use their words to communicate their feelings.

We also believe that children learn better through repetition, consistency and stability. During the genesis stage of a child's development it is better for them to master one skill at a time. It is often revealed that by looking at something more than once you begin to notice things that you did not see the first time. Sometimes a child may learn in more than one way to become proficient. By using various learning styles we can help the child meet their goals. It is extremely beneficial for a child to have consistent achievable challenges placed before him/her in order to boost morale. It is also important for the child to be in a safe environment where he/she has the room to move about and explore.  We feel these values are important to the development of a child in order to help them become independent.  For these skills to grow the center must make sure it creates an environment conducive to learning, such as:

    Reduce the number of transitions throughout the day.
    Ensure the environment feels safe for the child.
    Provide activities that are slightly challenging without       frustration. 
   Make learning fun.

The proper physical development of a child is fostered by the adults around them. Children look toward adults for answers and reassurance.  Adults must set goals and limits. We as adults, must encourage healthy living and discourage undesired lifestyles. It is important that we are positive examples of what we teach.  Children depend on adults to be their role models and provide stability.

During early development their social and emotional growth must be first be introduced to them by adults in their life. Adults must show them how bonds are formed. These bonds can be formed within the center by creating games, fostering their imagination and allowing them to outwardly communicate their feelings in a healthy way. Cognitive learning is achieved when adults create an environment in which children can understand spatial, perceptual, and attributive relationships.

We can confirm that the desirable behavior in learning has been mastered when the child can retell a short story with a vague concept of time; can count to 10 and knows how to recite the primary colors. Adults help to develop a moral development in a child by discouraging undesirable behavior through correction, apologies and redirection.

name: 1st Step Learning Academy L.L.C
details: “It Takes a Village to Raise a Child.” This saying translates into meaning that not just parents influence what a child becomes, but everything and everyone around him is an influence as well. It also means that all of the people in the village (community) have a responsibility in making sure that they are positive influences so that every child in that community reaches his or her full potential. Influences in a child’s life include the community (village) that he lives in including his immediate neighborhood, schools, daycares, teachers, neighbors, friends, family, church, organizations, and places he goes. But in addition to people and places media such as television and radio are a major influence in a child’s life as well.

name: Appletree Learning Center and Academy III
BB's 24 Hour Learning Center
details:
The idea for The Village was conceived in the late summer of 2013 by Blessed By Faith Online Communities, LLC. The name “The Village” is based on an African proverb, “It Takes a Village to Raise a Child”. This means not only are the parents responsible for influencing what a child becomes, but everyone else around them as well. The Village in modern terms would be a community. Although we are an online community we are dedicated to assisting in the healthy and successful upbringing of the children of the community.

The Village does not target a specific social class. It doesn’t matter if families visiting our site have a $15,000 annual income or a $250,000 income. Nor do we care if they are brown, red, white or blue. Instead, The Village celebrates the diversity of the world around us with the hope that through unity we will help and learn from each other and through our differences our community will become stronger as a whole. At The Village we believe that all children regardless of race, disability, religion, or economic background have a human right to equal opportunities that will lead them in the path of a successful future. Our main purpose is to insure that parents have knowledge of opportunities and services that will lead their children in the path to explore their dreams, talents and open the door to a future of unlimited success.

At The Village we assist parents by providing listings of businesses and organizations that specialize in services such as Child Care and Learning Centers, Special Needs Services, Private Education, Dance, Music and Arts, Sports, Clubs, Karate, Youth Organizations and Parent Training. There are a number of choices for each category listing, where there’s a match that will appeal to everyone. Blessed By Faith Online Communities, LLC pledges its dedication to our children. We do this by making an effort to aid in the future success of all the children that we serve. Because no child choses where they started from. But with the help of a strong community all children will have a choice in where or how far they go!

We use 3 major curriculum through the Abeka™, Creative, and High Scope programs, which are bridged together to form 1 academic unit for all students. In turn, kids learn more subjects at a higher rate and move on to new levels faster.
business hours: Monday–Friday, 6:00 a.m.–8:00 p.m. • Saturday, 9:00 a.m.–6:30 p.m. • Holiday Hours Available

name: Childcare Network #233 B
details: Childcare Network is the 4th largest for profit child care organization in North America.  With over 200 schools in 10 states, we are the leading early care and preschool education provider in the southern United States.  Our Childcare Network family is encompassed by over 25,000 families, and we truly feel that way! At Childcare Network, we engage our parents, local partners, and other advocates in our communities to provide high quality, age appropriate, and affordable early care and education for our children. We are there for our families as they maneuver through the joys and challenges of raising strong, caring, bright young children in this busy world. We go above and beyond to create safe teaching environments that allow parents to feel comfortable going to work each day while their child is with us. We deliver our high quality education, while striving to keep our costs less than other premium private child care providers. The directors at each location make sure that everything they do is done in a way that creates a positive experience for both parents and children in their school. Your family IS our family at Childcare Network, and we wouldn’t have it any other way!

name: Children's Leadership Academy
details:
Our academy is structured toward the commitment and high standards of EXCELLENCE as well as the DEVELOPMENT OF all CHILDREN.

Children’s Leadership Academy is a privately owned and operated preschool and child development center. We care for children from 6 weeks through 12 years old. Our child care facility is brand newly renovated, high tech, exceptionally clean, and designed to create an environment that is both educational and socially nurturing. Our vision is to prepare, strengthen and inspire children to be the future leaders of tomorrow.

Children’s Leadership Academy is committed to providing a safe, happy, and clean environment allowing children to have fun while learning and growing. All of our classrooms, hallways and playgrounds are monitored by a closed circuit video surveillance system. We have an open door visitation policy for our families, allowing you to come by at anytime throughout the day to observe your child. We use a keypad entry system to ensure the highest security and only giving access to those families that are currently enrolled. When you walk into our school you will immediately notice the warm, caring environment and our attention to detail and cleanliness.

name: Fayette Early Learning Academy
details:
Fayette Early Learning Academy offers high-quality education and childcare for infants, toddlers, and preschool-aged children. We also offer a School Aged program for children up to twelve (12) years of age, which converts to a full-day program whenever public schools are closed.

Our team is dedicated to improving the development of each child under our care, regardless of age group or learning ability. We use a high-quality, comprehensive learning program focused on each child’s physical, cognitive, and social/emotional needs at a pace that is appropriate his or her personal development—giving them the chance they need to succeed in school and in life.

At Fayette Early Learning Academy, we happily welcome children of all learning abilities!

details:
Four Seasons Montessori has been established to provide a safe, supportive, culturally-diverse learning environment guided by the educational philosophy of Dr. Maria Montessori.

At Four Seasons we seek to prepare children for life by guiding and supporting the individual child as they develop inner discipline, self-assurance, and a love of learning, while providing an environment in which they are free to explore, cooperate, create, and foster respect and a sense of responsibility to self, to others, and to the community. More about our curriculum.

name: Future Leaders Christian Academy Jonesboro
details: At the Future Leader's Christian Academy in Jonesboro, our mission is to dedicate ourselves to the enrichment of the entire family. We are devoted to empowering our parents, in addition to, providing excellent childcare. Our Atlanta, Jonesboro and Decatur private academies embrace the old adage that, “it takes village to raise a child” and we strongly believe in the importance of strong character, self worth, and spiritual wholeness. We place extreme emphasis on mental and social development. We measure our success by the holistic development of the children and strengthening of the families we enrich. We’re dedicated to being that important influential first step in a child becoming a Future Leader! We’re making the future brighter one mind at a time. Future Leaders Christian Academy; it’s not just our name, it’s our passion.

name: Jump Start Academy
details:
Our Mission -To Create a safe, nurturing, and loving environment that will prepare each child mentally, emotionally, socially, and physically for a life-long love of learning.

Our Philosophy - At Jump Start Academy, we are committed to providing quality care and education. We believe that all children should be taught about the world around them in a loving, nurturing, and caring environment. Children are the most precious gift we can be given. Their care and education depends on a trusting partnership between parents and caregivers. We want to build on what you as a parent are instilling in your child and inspire your child daily to explore new concepts and to try new things.

name: KIDazzle Child Care - Lowery
details: At KIDazzle Childcare Little Flyers Center parents and children come first! We believe that is it our job to extend and strengthen the foundation started at home. We provide a warm and nurturing environment while at the same time provide high quality education and child care for our most precious asset, our children. We use the Creative Curriculum, which allows for every child to pursue his or her special talents and to demonstrate their areas of strength. We want our children to feel that learning is an exciting lifelong experience that is full of wonder and fun!

name: Kiddos Inman
details:
Kiddos was built from a desire to take all the good I have seen in childcare, the business world, customer service and in the community and bundle it all together with out all the not so good stuff!

I wanted parents to walk in and love my teachers because they genuinely welcomed them, I never wanted to stop improving, I wanted to offer fair rates and scholarships for anyone who needed it, I wanted to have employees who loved their job and did it well and most of all I wanted to build a world that is designed with the Kids as our customer and I wanted a ton of kids!

Kiddos plans out each day to a T! Whether its our Summer Camp or one of our Year Round programs we map out a variety of choices for each hour we have kids. Our teachers are energetic, our Fun Fridays are a full production and we want our families to be fully immersed in our Kiddos family!

Kiddos first Day Camp started in the summer of 2010 where we started with about 18 kids and went to 75 kids in 3 weeks from just word of mouth! The last two summers we have had over 100 kids per day and a wait list SUMMER 2014 will be a BIG summer for us! We have the perfect team and are excited to begin our Camp Meccas ;) We will host Kiddos Summer Camps at the Sutton and Inman campuses! With camps for kids Ages 5-15!

Kiddos Day Camp will be back for our 4th summer- One at Inman and One at Sutton for elementary students, Kiddos Adventure Camp picks up at Sutton and is new for Middle Schoolers and we are partnering with over 25 of Atlanta's best Specialty Camps from our favorite extracurricular companies who will run 2 week camps for elementary and middle students!. THIS SUMMER WILL NOT BE SOMETHING YOU WANT TO MISS!!!

Kiddos also offers Year Round Programs! We offer After School programs at Rivers, Inman and Sutton as well as offer Extracurricular Classes at Garden Hills and Rivers.

We love what we do and we are so thankful for our families and that you took the time to learn more about us! Feel free to call or email with any questions! Check out our website for more information and of course to Register for SUMMER 2014

name: Kid's Depot
details: A Childcare Center providing a safe, developmentally appropriate environment for preschool and school age children. Our focus is to provide a stimulating early care and education experience.

name: KIP Academy
details:
At KIP Academy, we believe that learning should never end, because education is achieved, not received! We focus on building self-worth, self-knowledge, self-control, and self-confidence through "education first".

School has become increasingly difficult for students and families to navigate due to the pressure to excel on standardized tests without the support necessary for success. KIP Academy is the solution for working families. Our programs encourage students to learn, empowers them to become responsible, and helps them to develop socially. We give them the freedom to grow and explore in a safe, clean, structured and moral environment. With our small class sizes (1:10 and 1:15) and experienced committed staff, KIP Academy continues to set the standards and raise the bar for student learning.

name: La Petite Academy
details:
What Matters to Us
African American boy raising hand

New friendships. New ideas. New ways to learn.

Welcome to the joys of childhood. Welcome to La Petite Academy.

What matters to us at La Petite Academy is simple: Your child. Here, exceptionally strong, sound social and educational foundations are formed. Here, children learn to respect one another. Learn together. Learn to work together. Learn to have fun constructively.

And discover how enjoyable learning can be.

It all starts by design. The free-flowing, open concept design of our facilities inspires a nurturing, interactive, and collaborative environment in which your child can thrive. Our schools and classrooms are designed to give children room to grow, room to share and room to be themselves. At La Petite Academy, open spaces and open concepts promote open minds.

In addition, our entire school is designed to ensure that your child’s safety and security remain our top priority. And communication is essential. With regular updates (including many photos) of your child’s experiences, you can feel comfortable that you are sharing this journey – every step of the way.

name: Learning HIve Kids Club
details: Learning Hive, a community of licensed childcare programs, blends the safe cozy environment of a home with a unique atmosphere that depicts a structured educational essence. This is the edge that Learning Hive offers its families. At Learning Hive we use our own unique curriculum that is consistent with the developmentally appropriate practices for early childhood. Each educational suite at Learning Hive Centers follows a daily schedule – we adhere to the school of thought that children thrive in a structured and somewhat predictable environment. Our daily schedules allow children to set routines that foster caring bonds with other children and their teachers. This stems from the stability the schedules provide. The daily schedules are flexible enough to adapt to each child’s individual needs yet still offering a sense of consistency and security.﻿

name: Little Angels Learning Academy
details: Our goal is to provide and maintain a safe and nurturing learning environment for children. Our creative curriculum is designed to focus on the different developmental needs of children ages 6 weeks-4 years and after school children up to age 12 years. Daily lessons include but are not limited to, gross motor activities, pre-academics and academics, (Language Arts, math, Reading Readiness, Arts/Crafts, Music), and quiet play.

name: Little Angels Learning Center LLC
details: We offer a large variety of activities and developmental techniques to help our little ones grow cognitively, emotionally, physically and socially. We are open all year round and offer very flexible care. We pride ourselves on during our school year, Little Angels adheres to a Pre-School Comprehensive Curriculum. This curriculum is a fun and enjoyable way to introduce young children to early reading and language arts. Our Curriculum also helps children to identify each letter with a huggable letter person. All 26 letter people have their own special stories along with songs and are uniquely made just like each one of the children. We also incorporate math, science and social studies with the fun way of learning.

name: Ms. Pam's Precious Angels Family Childcare Center
Preferred School Care @ Kipp Strive
details: KIPP STRIVE Academy is a tuition-free public charter school located in the West End/Westview neighborhood in Atlanta. Founded in 2009, KIPP STRIVE Academy currently serves approximately 320 students in grades five through eight.  KIPP STRIVE Academy is a rigorous college preparatory school that is part of KIPP Metro Atlanta and the national KIPP network of schools preparing students for success in college and in life.

name: Preferred School Care @ Kipp Vision Primary
details: KIPP Vision Primary will open with a 100-seat kindergarten class in July 2013, adding one grade annually to reach full elementary school capacity in July of 2017. KIPP Vision will serve students in the same building as KIPP Vision Academy Middle School’s 5-8th grade, providing a cohesive K-8 pipeline to college for students in southeast Atlanta. KIPP Vision Primary will be established in Southeast Atlanta in the current KIPP Vision Academy Middle School facility.  KIPP Vision Primary will create a nurturing environment that cultivates in each student a passion for learning and a commitment to excellence. Through real life experiences, which leverage students’ innate abilities, and a rigorous curriculum, students will be empowered with the tools to build a better tomorrow for themselves, their families and their community. KIPP Vision Primary, like all KIPP schools, will be guided by the five KIPP pillars: high expectations, choice and commitment, more time, power to lead, and a focus on results.

name: Primary Prep
details: We believe in the development of the whole child.  Our curriculum is designed to focus on the creative, emotional, intellectual, physical, and social growth of each individual.  The purpose of our approach is to foster competency in the young child.  While the emphasis is on children, family involvement is encouraged and supported. Our mission is To develop the whole child, by providing a stimulation early care and educational experience.  Helping to promote each child’s social, emotional, physical and cognitive development individually.  Providing an eco-friendly environment and an organic lifestyle.  To help with obesity in children by giving them alternatives on food choices and helping create a love for the environment.

details: Primrose is an accredited private preschool that provides a premier educational child care experience. The Leader in Educational Child Care®, we partner with parents to help children build the right foundation for future learning and life. Our goal is to help children have fun while building Active Minds, Healthy Bodies and Happy Hearts®.

Our schools provide a safe “home away from home” environment for the developmental growth of every child. name: Rambam Day School
details:
Welcome to Rambam Day School located in Historic Savannah, Georgia. Our city has one of the oldest Jewish Communities in the Southeast. Founded in 1990, Rambam continues the tradition of outstanding Jewish Day Schools. Our co-educational elementary and middle school proudly serves the entire Jewish community - Orthodox, Conservative and Reform.

Jewish education is the most effective method of maintaining your child's Jewish identity and instilling cultural values. Our goal is to nurture and feed our community's young Jewish members, thus ensuring these values are passed down to future generations.

name: Renee's Kid's World 2 LLC
details: OUR GOAL IS TO HELP EACH CHILD EXCEL IN ALL AREAS OF DEVELOPMENT; PHYSICAL, SOCIAL, EMOTIONAL, AND COGNITIVE BY INSPIRING THEM TO EXPLORE THE WORLD WITH CONFIDENCE IN A STIMULATING, NURTURING, ENVIRONMENT WITH A VARIETY OF INTEREST AREAS SUCH AS: ART, SCIENCE, DRAMATIC PLAY, MANIPULATIVES, STORY TIME, OUTSIDE PLAY, E.T.C. RENEE'S KIDS WORLD IS WHERE CHILDREN ARE ALLOWED TO BE CHILDREN!

name: Sprayberry 2.0 Inc.
details: Our goal at Sprayberry Academy is to make certain your child receives the opportunity to attain a well-rounded education. By providing them with a fun and educational environment, they will gain the skills they require to be successful in life.

name: Sugar Bears Learning Center
details:
Sugar Bears Learning Center is dedicated to a loving, safe and friendly learning environment for your child and peace of mind for the parents.

We will incorporate daily teaching with encouragement and fun objectives to focus on your child’s age appropriate development. These will include social, emotional, physical, cognitive and spiritual areas.

 Our daily time together will include prayer, scripture teachings and Bible verses along with learning numbers, letters and colors. These practices will help instill patience, the love of God, self control and love for others. We will also be teaching basic manners such as “please”, “thank you”, “you’re welcome” and of course “yes” and “no” “ma’am” and “sir”.

We hope that you will consider Sugar Bears Learning Center a second home and we encourage parent and grandparent participation in our learning and sharing.

name: Taylors Tiny Tots Learning Center  Inc.
The Children's Academy
details: We offer all day childcare with a strong educational emphasis. We are taking applications for children. We have openings for all ages 6 weeks to 4 years old. Our 3/4 year old room will be set up in school style. Each room follows a daily schedule that is posted in each room. Feel free to stop by for a tour of our facilities!

name: The Goddard School
details: Welcome! Our goal is to be a resource to you and your family, while creating a community where parents can share information and learn from each other. The Goddard School uses the most current, academically endorsed methods to ensure that children have fun while learning the skills they need for long-term success in school and in life. Our talented teachers also collaborate with parents to nurture children into respectful, confident and joyful learners. Our year-round program offers families the choice of either a half- or a full-day schedule.

name: The Lime Light
details: The Lime Light is a privately owned preschool, for ages 3-5. located in Manchester, GA. We offer a bright, clean, happy facility that will make you feel welcomed the moment you walk through the doors. Cyd Brantley, Ed.S. is the owner. She is a certified teacher, holding a Specialists degree in Early Childhood Education and drawing from more than 25 years of experience in the classroom. We pride ourselves in being instrumental in fostering a love for learning that will follow your child throughout life. If you are looking for a premier school setting for your three through five year-old, please call us at 706-846-LIME.

name: The Rock Schoolage Center
details: The Rock is Brunswick's school age community of young achievers. We provide after school programs for children of the ages 6-12. Our after school programs were founded by Mr. and Mrs. Dickerson. Natives of Brunswick Georgia Mr. and Mrs. Dickerson are entrepreneurs with a heart for the youth in the community who thrives for perfection and setting the standard for young achievers.

name: The Stone Academy
details:
Stone Academy, Inc. is an academically enriching afterschool and summer program located in the Historic Booker T. Washington Center. We are deeply committed to making a significant, positive, and lasting contribution to the education of all children. Our vision is to be a Stone of hope, where children enjoy learning, through student-centered learning, rather than teacher centered learning. The mission of Stone Academy is to provide 21st Century children with 21st Century Curriculum S.T.E.A.M. (Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Math). In Bibb County, many of our children did not meet the standard in reading. Stone Academy is committed to increase the reading levels of students’ ages 5-18 years old, along with all major disciplines.

To ensure the success of our children, Stone Academy has fostered relationships with the Bibb County School System, community leaders and other organizations in a holistic effort to meet student needs. Mercer University, Savannah State University, and Wingate University, are intricately involved in our effort, providing tutoring, mentoring, service learning, and volunteering in an effort to aid in children realizing their dreams and attaining them.

name: The Tutor Shop at Dolvin ES
details:
The Tutor Shop is a unique tutoring company established upon the belief that all children should be given an equal opportunity to learn. With a combined 80 years of teaching, administration, and marketing experience, the three principals of the company realized that success could greatly be increased if the lessons catered to the student's individual needs.

The Tutor Shop is a boutique-type tutoring company comprised of only the finest, highly qualified teachers. Unlike other tutoring companies who require a student to work within their specific guidelines and programs, The Tutor Shop utilizes the student’s own curriculum. The Tutor Shop does not require parents to purchase materials or pay for additional testing.

Offering admissions interview counseling, one-on-one tutoring, summer camps, and an after school program, as well as ACT/SAT test prep, The Tutor Shop provides a wide variety of tutoring options that help students realize their full potential.

name: To The Top Youth Center
details: To The Top Youth Center is designed to provide safe and secure after school and out of school facility for children of all faiths, cultures, and socioeconomic backgrounds. While doing so we will provide the youth a safe and nurturing facility to socialize with peers, receive assistance with their homework and receive mentorship and guidance on post secondary education choices. The youth also learn life skills needed to being an effective member of the society they live in. Our program also offer controlled after hour’s activities. Our goal is to promote the development of our children and youth into healthy, productive, lifelong learners.

name: Toddler University
details: It is our mission to provide quality care for children and families here in Atlanta and surrounding areas. Our learning program exists to provide infants to toddlers & preschoolers to school-age children with a warm, loving environment where he or she can feel safe, secure and happy. Our staff members are carefully screened and certified in early childhood education. Toddler University is licensed and adheres to the highest standards of security, safety, cleanliness and teaching. Our classrooms reflect the spirit of children and support their developmental needs. We prepare the environment so that it offers stimulating, challenging materials and activities. Every day we work to make education fun!! We provide excellent childcare and affordable rates to our families. We work in partnership with parents and families to build mutual understanding and always welcome your participation. Our staff is dedicated to providing the most comfortable and happy environment for your children. Our program not only stimulates educational growth but, most important, ensures love, acceptance and safety to all the children.

name: Trinity AME Early Learning Center
details:
We believe that in order for our children to achieve their fullest potential, our instructions should be designed
for the development of the whole child.  We believe that each child’s physical and mental health should be
properly nurtured.  We intend to execute our program so as to produce an environment that is conducive to
the development of a value system that builds a foundation which promotes high self-esteem and
appropriate positive self-confidence.

name: Troyce's Childcare and Private School
details: "A Cut Above Childcare"

name: Twinkle Twinkle Little Star Childcare and Learning Center
Wade Walker Park YMCA After School Program
details: Our programs are designed to offer each child many opportunities for intellectual, physical and social development. Children take part in a wide variety of group and individual activities including art, enrichment components, homework time and sports. Periodically, we may have special guests and family events. We offer a quality program that includes planned activities to compliment the school experience. Our highest goal is a warm, safe and caring atmosphere for children.The Wade Walker Park Family YMCA After School Program is administered by the Program Directors at our branch. Our After School Program is staffed by trained, qualified personnel who meet YMCA and state standards. We hire our staff through a careful selection process which includes a criminal background check and drug testing . We maintain staff stability and minimize transition for the children. Our staff to child ratio is maintained at an average of 1 to 15.

name: Waverly Hall Christian Academy Daycare and LC
details:
It is our desire at Waverly Hall Christian Academy to provide an academically excellent education in a thoroughly Christian environment.

We believe that we can educate the mind; however, if we neglect the education of the soul and spirit, then we have neglected the whole person. Waverly Hall Christian Academy is a ministry that God has brought to fruition through the vision and hard work of His people — the board of directors, the administration, and the staff.

We invite you to share our vision of being a “light in our community.” Your support of, prayer for, and commitment to Waverly Hall Christian Academy will surely reap benefits for everyone involved. Help us “prepare tomorrow’s leaders today.”

name: We Care Academy
details: The mission of We Care Academy is to provide safe, affordable, quality child care for the Rockdale and surrounding communities. In doing so, we support families in their efforts to work and/or attend school. We CareAcademy provide a program for children ages six weeks to twelve years. We provide a safe, clean environment where children are encouraged to develop at their own pace. The We Care staff is committed to the families we serve, providing support and encouragement.

name: YMCA Afterschool Enrichment Program @ C.H. Gullatt Elementary Sch
YMCA at Saddle Ridge Elementary and Middle School
details: We are a proud provider of on-site after school programs, serving five locations within Catoosa and Walker Counties. At each program location, students follow a curriculum developed by the YMCA to include daily activities in academics, physical fitness and healthy eating. Programs are lead by qualified directors age 21 and older and counselors and volunteers age 18 and older. Staff are trained according to licensing guidelines and specifically to meet the individual needs of children in the program.

name: YMCA Prime Time - Hightower Elementary
details: With a focus on safety, health, social growth and academic enhancement, Y afterschool programs serve kindergartners through middle schoolers with a variety of programmatic and activity options to explore and develop their interests and talents.

name: YMCA Pryme Tyme - The STEM Academy
details:
Pryme Tyme is that special time before school and at the end of school for children whose parents are at work. The YMCA can make this a great time to grow, to play and to be with friends. Pryme Tyme is held at the school your child attends. Hours are from 7:00 a.m. until the start of school and the end of school until 6:00 p.m.
 
Pryme Tyme programs are not just supervised playgrounds. We strive to maintain a ratio that provides plenty of individual attention as well as small group activity.

name: YWCO After School at Malcom Bridge Elementary School
details:
The Athens YWCO is a non-profit community agency promoting healthy lifestyles for adults and kids through various fitness, aquatic, after school and summer camp programs. Our facility is located on Research Drive just off the UGA campus and offers numerous opportunities for swimming, fitness classes, pilates reformer, a walking trail, and a summer day camp. In Oconee County we run state licensed after school programs in several of the Oconee Elementary Schools.

The Athens YWCO also hosts and promotes  youth and family activities such as the annual Kids Tri the Y Youth Triathlon, the USA Triathlon Splash and Dash and the Hop and Hunt 5k.

name: Zion Learning Academy
details: A Christian based academy with a clean, loving, safe, and an educational environment for children ages 6 weeks to 13 years of age.

name: Fort Gordon Child Development Services @ the West
details:
Army Child Development Centers (CDC) are known as the “benchmark for the Nation” and we are committed to upholding this national statement, while supporting the families of the Fort Gordon community.

The Ft. Gordon West CDC provides a consistent, safe, and nurturing environment for children. Our curriculum and age appropriate activities promote the social, emotional, physical, creative and cognitive growth of your child. All programs are staffed with competent, trained and nurturing Program Assistants and Education Technicians.

name: McEver Arts Academy
details: McEver Arts Academy's Media Center strives to empower the learning community to use information, ideas, and technology ethically, creatively,and critically in order to become lifelong learners and to promote enthusiasm and enjoyment of reading.

name: Princeton Academy
details:
At Princeton Academy, we have programs for children ages six weeks to 12 years designed specifically by experts in the field of early childhood education.
From infancy to preschool to Kindergarten, at Princeton Academy your child will engage in exciting learning activities specifically designed to meet their developmental needs and help them advance to the next level. We focus on:

    Instilling and extending language and vocabulary
    Developing fine and gross motor skills
    Fostering critical thinking
    Encouraging positive social interactions
    Nurturing creativity and curiosity

At Princeton Academy, you'll find dedicated teachers practicing focused curricula in classrooms that are clean and, most importantly, safe.

name: Stark Elementary School
details:
Stark Elementary is one of three elementary schools in Butts County.  Stark currently enrolls approximately 670 students. Our mascot is the Eagle and our school colors are maroon and tan. 

Highlights:
    North Mulberry Elementary Was Renamed Stark Elementary in 2008.
    North Mulberry Elementary School was recognized as a "Pay for Performance" school for the years 2002-03 and 2003-04.
    "Distinguished Title I" school in 2004 for meeting Adequate Yearly Progress(AYP) for 3 years.
    "Distinguished Title I" school in 2005 and received $12,492.00 for meeting Adequate Yearly Progress(AYP) for 4 years.
    North Mulberry Elementary School met AYP for 8 years.
    "State of Georgia Governor's Office of Student Achievement Silver Award" in 2005.
    Chosen as a stop on the 14th Annual Georgia Partnership for Excellence in Education bus tour.

We have achieved much to be recognized. We are very proud of the Stark Elementary School faculty, staff, students, and parents! Thank you for your support.
